<div id="review_1970427945" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1970427945" />
    <a title="Nick Borrelli" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5427149-nick-borrelli"><img alt="Nick Borrelli" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618861498p2/5427149.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1970427945?book_show_action=true">Apr 13, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nick Borrelli" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nick Borrelli" href="/user/show/5427149-nick-borrelli">Nick Borrelli</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1970427945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer996821604867035506">Too much of a soap opera read for me. I was under the impression that this was a pretty decent story that was tightly connected with the events of the Civil War as the backdrop. What I realized pretty quickly was that the story is the main focus and the Civil War part is just there for convenience. That&apos;s fine if the story is a compelling one or an interesting one. Unfortunately, I was disinterested in the fates of the Hazards and Mains fairly quickly and then I was left with nothing to hang my </span>
  <span id="freeText996821604867035506" style="display:none">Too much of a soap opera read for me. I was under the impression that this was a pretty decent story that was tightly connected with the events of the Civil War as the backdrop. What I realized pretty quickly was that the story is the main focus and the Civil War part is just there for convenience. That's fine if the story is a compelling one or an interesting one. Unfortunately, I was disinterested in the fates of the Hazards and Mains fairly quickly and then I was left with nothing to hang my hat on. Needless to say, it wasn't what I was looking for and I will not be picking up books two and three.</span>
  <a data-text-id="996821604867035506" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

