      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/5768.John_Jakes">About John Jakes</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/5768.John_Jakes"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1342709158p3/5768.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/5768.John_Jakes">John Jakes
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
745
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer3705257329173316556"><b>John William Jakes</b>, the author of more than a dozen novels, is regarded as one of today’s most distinguished writers of historical fiction. His work includes the highly acclaimed Kent Family Chronicles series and the North and South Trilogy. Jakes’s commitment to historical accuracy and evocative storytelling earned him the title of “the godfather of historical novelists” from the Los Angeles Time</span>
  <span id="freeText3705257329173316556" style="display:none"><b>John William Jakes</b>, the author of more than a dozen novels, is regarded as one of today’s most distinguished writers of historical fiction. His work includes the highly acclaimed Kent Family Chronicles series and the North and South Trilogy. Jakes’s commitment to historical accuracy and evocative storytelling earned him the title of “the godfather of historical novelists” from the Los Angeles Times and led to a streak of sixteen consecutive New York Times bestsellers. Jakes has received several awards for his work and is a member of the Authors Guild and the PEN American Center. He and his wife, Rachel, live on the west coast of Florida.<br /><br />Also writes under pseudonyms <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1396149._Jay_Scotland" title=" Jay Scotland" rel="nofollow noopener"> Jay Scotland</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/2117002.Alan_Payne" title="Alan Payne" rel="nofollow noopener">Alan Payne</a>, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/14173062.Rachel_Ann_Payne" title="Rachel Ann Payne" rel="nofollow noopener">Rachel Ann Payne</a>, Robert Hart Davis, Darius John Granger, John Lee Gray. Has ghost written as William Ard.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3705257329173316556" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>
